40|$|The {{design of}} {{alerting}} systems integrating various technologies (mobile, satellite, navigation), capable to reach anytime and anywhere population, is becoming of absolute importance for management of tomorrow crisis situations. In this respect, the paper explores the design implications arising when <b>alert</b> <b>messages</b> are sent over Global Navigation Satellite Services (GNSS). Extensions of GNSS system to transport <b>alert</b> <b>messages</b> are presented. The performance evaluation {{given at the}} end of the paper shows the efficiency of the design system in terms of average <b>alert</b> <b>message</b> delivery delay and confirms the potential of GNSS systems for future alert applications...|$|R
