40|$|International audienceTraffic safety through inter-vehicular {{communication}} {{is one of}} the most promising and challenging applications of Vehicular Ad-hoc Networks. In this context, information such as position, direction, and speed, is often broadcast by vehicles so as to facilitate fast multi-hop propagation of possible <b>alert</b> <b>messages.</b> Unfortunately, a malicious vehicle can inject bogus information or cheat about its position. In this work, we analyze the impact of a position cheating attack on an <b>alert</b> <b>message</b> application. We show that this weakness we found could be leveraged by an adversary in a very effective way. Furthermore, our analysis leads us to design a countermeasure to this threat. Finally, we run a set of simulations which confirm our findings...|$|R
